15/02/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Stipe Mesic will be inaugurated for his second five-year term as president at a formal ceremony in Zagreb on Friday (18 February), according to an announcement Monday.
Mesic defeated rival Jadranka Kosor in a run-off last month.
In other news, EU Integration Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic visited Bratislava and met with Slovakian Deputy Prime Minister Pal Csaky on Monday.
Grabar-Kitarovic was assured of Slovakia's full support for Croatia's EU membership bid.
(HINA, HRT - 14/02/05)
